Description: Modern container and virtual machine manager - client
 Incus is a modern system container, application container and virtual
 machine manager. It provides a cloud-like environment, creating instances
 from premade images or any Docker (OCI) registry and offers a wide variety
 of features, including the ability to seamlessly cluster servers together.
 .
 It supports multiple different local or remote storage options, traditional
 or fully distributed networking and offers most common cloud features,
 including a full REST API and integrations with common tooling like Ansible,
 Terraform/OpenTofu, Packr, and Kubernetes Cluster API.
 .
